Source: picam-frontend
Section: web
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jaco Hanekom <jhanekom@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               cmake,
               pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: picam-frontend
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Multi-Pi web viewer for picam-orchestrator backends
 Single web UI that can view and switch between multiple picam-orchestrator
 backends (one per Pi) from a single page. Proxies MJPEG frames and
 status JSON through itself — browsers never connect directly to any
 Pi, only to this frontend, which then reaches out to whichever
 backend is currently selected.
 .
 Configure the list of Pis in /etc/picam-frontend/config.ini under
 the [pis] section. Each Pi just needs picam-orchestrator installed and
 reachable on the network; no other configuration is required on
 the Pi side.
 .
 Open http://<this-host> in a browser to view.
 .
 Config: /etc/picam-frontend/config.ini
